31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=285965";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:574:"<p>The past three weeks have been a blur-  the release of 3.8.9beta, bursting at the seams with new features, bug fixes and refactored code&#8230; brand new support products and da da da da!  WP  e-Commerce hit the 2 million downloads mark on the WordPress repository. What 2 Million Means WPEC has come so far.. as [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/shipping/2-million-download-later-hey-let-us-get-that-for-you/">2 Million Download Later&#8230; Hey, Let us Get That For You!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"amandablum";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4762:"<p><a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/2million.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-285979 aligncenter" title="2millionWPe-commercedownloads" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/2million.jpg" alt="" width="460" height="144" /></a></p>\n<p>The past three weeks have been a blur-  the release of<a href="http://getshopped.org/payment-gateways/wpec-dev-update-3-8-9-ready-for-beta-testing/"> 3.8.9beta</a>, bursting at the seams with new features, bug fixes and refactored code&#8230; brand new support products and da da da da!  WP  e-Commerce hit the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/">2 million downloads</a> mark on the WordPress repository.</p>\n<h5><span id="more-285965"></span>What 2 Million Means</h5>\n<p>WPEC has come so far.. as WordPress has grown up, we&#8217;ve grown up alongside it; as WordPress has changed, we&#8217;ve adjusted to change with it- bringing custom post types, widgets, shortcodes and taxonomy to WPEC. We&#8217;ve helped 2 million people launch stores- launch new livelihoods, support their families, help pay for school, launch new ideas, raise money for important causes. We are so proud.. of YOU. We are just the tool, our users make our tool something greater.</p>\n<blockquote><p>We&#8217;ve helped 2 million people launch stores- launch new livelihoods, support their families, help pay for school, launch new ideas, raise money for important causes.</p></blockquote>\n<p>E-Commerce has grown up too- there are so many options that you can be easily overwhelmed and asking WordPress to become a full fledged store is not a small thing. That said- our team is as committed as ever to the idea that WordPress is still the easiest and most fully featured CMS available and that we can provide a free, fully featured store plugin for WordPress users. We&#8217;re not just the most popular because we&#8217;ve been around the longest- WP e-Commerce remains the most fully featured WordPress e-Commerce tool on the market. We are devoted to making our tool even easier to use this year with improved UI, features for both users and developers and a slew of new Add Ons.</p>\n<h5>Supporting Our Users</h5>\n<p>The rave reviews for our improved support system continue to roll in. While a full support staff tackles our <a href="http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/">Premium One on One Support</a> questions, the <a href="http://getshopped.org/forums/">community forums</a> have new life. A month into our experiment, our developer network is actively engaging with our users and everyone seems happier!  Now we want to make it even easier- you&#8217;ll notice new support avenues for WP e-Commerce&#8230; our support staff will happily <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/37wpecupgrade/">upgrade your installation</a>,<a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-service/wp-e-commerce-installation-gold-cart/"> install Gold Cart</a> for you or any of our <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-service/wpec-add-on-installation/">other Premium Add Ons</a>. If you think you may need more help with your WP e-Commerce store, you can even purchase <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/gold-cart-plugin-duplicate/">additional support tokens</a> now. As always, our Premium support staff will work with you to get things up and running as fast as possible.</p>\n<h5>3.8.9beta</h5>\n<p>We&#8217;ve had tons of people testing 3.8.9 for us, and so far the reviews are awesome! People are loving the changes made to variations, and are discovering that the refactored code has solved all kinds of random issues users have had in the past. The shipping advancements have had a real impact on our store owners- its easier to set up than ever and our new presentation settings really impress our users. Colorbox integration seems to be a fan favorite- and the Google Analytics update is a win for everyone. We&#8217;re a week or two away from the final release, so keep testing!</p>\n<h5>Where Do We Go From Here?</h5>\n<p>The next year will be so exciting for WPEC users we almost can&#8217;t breathe trying to keep the surprises a secret. We know what we&#8217;re planning, but we&#8217;d love to know what YOU want. We get requests for features and plugins all the time and you&#8217;ve seen those requests turn into actual features and plugins. So&#8230; how can we better serve you as we make the long, final march to WP e-Commerce 4.0?</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/shipping/2-million-download-later-hey-let-us-get-that-for-you/">2 Million Download Later&#8230; Hey, Let us Get That For You!</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"http://getshopped.org/shipping/2-million-download-later-hey-let-us-get-that-for-you/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"14";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:44:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n			\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"Hey Hey Hey, Goodbye… to WP e-Commerce 3.7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:84:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/hey-hey-hey-goodbye-to-wp-e-commerce-3-7/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:93:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/hey-hey-hey-goodbye-to-wp-e-commerce-3-7/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Sep 2012 22:51:08 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:20:"WP e-Commerce Plugin";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"3.7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"http://getshopped.org/?p=284306";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:576:"<p>IE 6, Kubrick Theme, Flash splash pages, comic sans&#8230; all items that eventually age out. The past 18 months have been instrumental in developing new code and features for WPEC and during that time we&#8217;ve helped literally hundreds of thousands of users move from WP e-Commerce 3.7 to 3.8. For our users, the difference is [...]</p><p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/hey-hey-hey-goodbye-to-wp-e-commerce-3-7/">Hey Hey Hey, Goodbye&#8230; to WP e-Commerce 3.7</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"amandablum";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7699:"<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-285498" title="Goodbye WPEC 3.7!" src="http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/graves2.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="250" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ie6countdown.com/">IE 6</a>, <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/themes/default">Kubrick Theme</a>, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MuAGpW5Jo14">Flash splash pages</a>, <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OBibXwwLBts&amp;feature=player_embedded">comic sans</a>&#8230; all items that eventually age out. The past 18 months have been instrumental in developing new code and features for WPEC and during that time we&#8217;ve helped literally hundreds of thousands of users move from WP e-Commerce 3.7 to 3.8. For our users, the difference is huge!</p>\n<p>Now that 3.8 is about 18 months old, <strong>we&#8217;re going to be officially dropping support for WP e-Commerce 3.7 as of September 1</strong> <span id="more-284306"></span>.Soooooo&#8230; now:)  This can be upsetting to people, but in order to develop NEW products and features, eventually companies must depreciate support for older products that take up too many resources.  The average 3.7 ticket requires about 4-5 hours of support time and does our users a disservice since <a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.8.5.zip">WP e-Commerce is free to upgrade</a> and chock full of features, better code base and more capability.  Try to remember that any website, even in WordPress, probably needs a refresh every few years&#8230; a new theme or upgrading of features such as plugins to custom post types, etc. We&#8217;ll try to make it easier for you.</p>\n<h5>What does that mean?</h5>\n<p>WPEC add ons and themes won&#8217;t be required to support 3.7 anymore. When you register for support with our <a href="http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/">Premium </a><a href="http://getshopped.org/resources/premium-support/">One on One Support</a>, we won&#8217;t work on 3.7 installations, you&#8217;ll need to upgrade to 3.8 first.</p>\n<h5>What if I&#8217;m Still Using 3.7?</h5>\n<p>As with all software, if you don&#8217;t upgrade consistently, you may find yourself scarily out of date. Trying to upgrade from 3.7 to the current release may actually break your installation. Its like trying to upgrade from WordPress 2.7 to 3.0. Its a big leap and you may need to make some ministeps in between.</p>\n<h5>I&#8217;m scared to Upgrade</h5>\n<p>We understand. Don&#8217;t worry, we&#8217;ve got your back. Either you can upgrade using our guides, or <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/37wpecupgrade/">we can do it for you.</a> If you just follow the guide and our troubleshooting guide, you&#8217;ll likely be able to do it yourself. Try to remember though&#8230; there are a number of variables here: an older theme, older plugins, perhaps an updated WordPress not compatible with 3.7 that someone hacked to make things work&#8230; So, if you&#8217;d prefer <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/37wpecupgrade/">we do it for you</a>, skip ahead.</p>\n<h5>Steps to Upgrading WPEC 3.7 to current</h5>\n<p>0. backup your website<br />\n1. Make sure WordPress is current<br />\n2. Activate the default theme<br />\n3. Deactivate all plugins except WPEC<br />\n4. Upgrade to 3.7.7 (<a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.7.7.zip">Available here</a>). When prompted, upgrade database.<br />\n5. Upgrade to 3.8.3 (<a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.3.zip">Available here</a>). When prompted, upgrade database.<br />\n6. Upgrade to 3.8.5 (<a href="http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.5.zip">Available here</a>). When prompted, upgrade database.<br />\n7. Upgrade to current version (<a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/wp-e-commerce/">available here</a>, or from plugins menu). If prompted, upgrade database.<br />\n8. Check your installation on the front end. Is the products page there? Are the products all there? Attempt to checkout. Make sure your payment gateway still works, particularly if its custom.<br />\n9. If everything works, then the upgrade was successful. Now its time to test your theme and plugins. Activate your theme. Try the front end and test the products pages, single products pages, and try checking out. If there are any problems at this point, we know it is a theme issue. Your options are to switch themes, or to fix what is wrong with yours. Consider a developer to help you from our consultants list, or perhaps try asking for help in our community forums. Remember, these are not monitored by staff, but by community members.<br />\n10. If your theme works fine, now its time to start activating other plugins. If you&#8217;ve waited to upgrade them, start now. Activate plugins one by one and test the site.<br />\n11. If this works- then congratulations! You&#8217;ve upgraded successfully. Take a deep breath, grab a drink and kick back. Cheers!<br />\n12. Or just <a href="http://getshopped.org/premium-upgrades/premium-plugin/37wpecupgrade/">hire us to do it instead</a>! Have professional WP e-Commerce staff take care of your upgrade.</p>\n<h5>If there is an issue, consider these troubleshooting tips</h5>\n<p>Deactivate all your plugins and put on the default 2010 theme. If the problem is resolved then activate your plugins one at a time checking for the issue. Once you find it that plugin is causing the conflict, if all your plugins are fine then switch your theme.</p>\n<p>Ensure your using the latest 3.8 templates: Copy the templates located inside the wpsc-templates folder (inside the main WPEC plugin)  into your currently activated theme folder and flush the theme cache. To flush the theme cache you need to go to the presentation settings page and push the flush theme cache button located in the advanced theme settings metabox.</p>\n<p>Ensure all your premium plugins are up to date &#8211; if you have premium plugins from GetShopped and would like the latest version you can submit a<a href="http://getshopped.org/extend/premium-upgrades-files/"> form here</a> and we&#8217;ll send your files over.</p>\n<p>Ensure all your other plugins are up to date.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re having problems with your checkout page try turning off your shipping and deselecting your shipping modules. If your checkout now works then you have a problem with your shipping module.</p>\n<p>Ensure your Gold Cart is still activated on the store upgrades page, if it&#8217;s not, try entering in your API Key and Name- this can be found on your purchase receipt. If you can&#8217;t get this key to activate you may need to reset it first. If your still having problems then let us know via <a href="http://getshopped.org/api-key-questions-and-problems/">this form</a>.</p>\n<p>Missing products? Have you run the database upgrade? When you first activate 3.8 you will need to run a database upgrade your products wont appear until they have been transferred over to their new custom post type- you&#8217;ll be prompted to do this the first time you sign back into your site after upgrade.</p>\n<p>If you want to go back to 3.7 for whatever reason you can always just reactivate the old plugin (You can copy it from your backup <img src=''http://getshopped.org/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif'' alt='':)'' class=''wp-smiley'' />  ), when your database is upgraded the old product format will remain.</p>\n<p>The post <a href="http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/hey-hey-hey-goodbye-to-wp-e-commerce-3-7/">Hey Hey Hey, Goodbye&#8230; to WP e-Commerce 3.7</a> appeared first on <a href="http://getshopped.org">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:89:"http://getshopped.org/wp-e-commerce-plugin/hey-hey-hey-goodbye-to-wp-e-commerce-3-7/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2:"19";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:4:"href";s:57:"http://getshopped.org/category/wp-e-commerce-plugin/feed/";s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"hourly";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:15:"updateFrequency";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";